      <h2 id="rdfUris">Suggested RDF URIs</h2>

      <p>
        Every data element carries a <strong>suggested RDF URI</strong> using the
        <code>https://opda.org.uk/pdtf/</code> base namespace — not yet registered or
        dereferenced, but stable enough to use in draft ontology work.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Entities (objects / classes): <code>https://opda.org.uk/pdtf/<em>ClassName</em></code> (flat — no <code>/class/</code> segment)</li>
        <li>Properties (scalar attributes): <code>https://opda.org.uk/pdtf/<em>propertyName</em></code> (flat — no <code>/vocab/</code> segment)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        These will be refined when the upper ontology is defined (see step 2 under
        <a href="#nextSteps">What to do with these deliverables</a>). Cross-context concepts
        (e.g., <code>address</code>, <code>name</code>) share a single URI — disambiguation
        into context-specific sub-properties is deferred to that step.
      </p>

      <h2 id="sourcesCited">Source citations</h2>

      <p>
        Every entry in the browser carries a <strong>source</strong> field (primary schema) and a
        <strong>sources</strong> array listing all schemas that define that path. Use the
        Sources facet to explore which overlays contribute a given element.
      </p>

      <p>The primary sources, with paths:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><a class="resource-link" href="/resource?path=source/03-standards/schemas/src/schemas/v3/pdtf-transaction.json"><code>source/03-standards/schemas/src/schemas/v3/pdtf-transaction.json</code></a> (base transaction schema)</li>
        <li><code>source/03-standards/schemas/src/schemas/v3/overlays/*.json</code> (BASPI v5, TA6, TA7, TA10, NTS2, NTSL2, CON29R, CON29DW, PIQ, RDS, OC1, LLC1, LPE1, FME1, SR24)</li>
        <li><a class="resource-link" href="/resource?path=source/06-research/trust-framework-poc/Glossary.xlsx"><code>source/06-research/trust-framework-poc/Glossary.xlsx</code></a></li>
        <li><a class="resource-link" href="/resource?path=source/04-governance-bodies/working-groups/technical/Glossary.xlsx"><code>source/04-governance-bodies/working-groups/technical/Glossary.xlsx</code></a></li>
        <li>External: <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/vc-data-model-2.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">W3C VCDM 2.0</a>, <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/did-1.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">W3C DID 1.0</a>, <a href="https://trustoverip.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Trust Over IP Foundation</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="crossContext">Cross-context concepts</h2>

      <p>
        Many paths appear in three or more overlays — these are the <strong>cross-context
        vocabulary</strong> that needs explicit reconciliation in the ontology.
        Top examples (sorted by spread):
      </p>

      <p>
        <code>address</code>, <code>name</code>, <code>date</code>, <code>amount</code>,
        <code>type</code>, <code>description</code>, <code>reference</code>,
        <code>status</code>, <code>provider</code>, <code>title</code>,
        <code>property</code>, <code>id</code>, <code>required</code>, <code>code</code>,
        <code>category</code> …
      </p>

      <p>
        Full list with which overlays contain each: see the
        "Cross-context concepts" section of
        <a class="resource-link" href="/resource?path=source/00-deliverables/semantic-models/business-glossary.md"><code>source/00-deliverables/semantic-models/business-glossary.md</code></a>.
      </p>

      <h2 id="nextSteps">What to do with these deliverables</h2>

      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Have an editorial pass over <a class="resource-link" href="/resource?path=source/00-deliverables/semantic-models/business-glossary.md" title="source/00-deliverables/semantic-models/business-glossary.md"><code>business-glossary.md</code></a></strong>
          with the Technical Working Group — reconcile the OPDA Glossary terms with the
          property-data terms extracted from the schemas.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Define the upper ontology</strong> — pick the core classes (Transaction,
          Property, Participant, Claim, Document, Form, Search) and align with W3C VC.
          Register the <code>https://opda.org.uk/pdtf/</code> namespace and replace the
          suggested URIs with resolvable ones.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Per-overlay JSON-LD contexts</strong> — for each of the
          <a href="/modelling/overlays">16 canonical overlays</a>, author a <code>@context</code>
          that maps JSON property names to ontology terms. Start with
          <a class="resource-link" href="/resource?path=source/03-standards/schemas/src/schemas/v3/overlays/baspi5.json" title="source/03-standards/schemas/src/schemas/v3/overlays/baspi5.json"><code>baspi5.json</code></a> as the worked example.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Generate SHACL shapes</strong> from the JSON Schema validation rules.
          Most rules (required, enum, pattern, type) translate mechanically.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Disambiguate cross-context names</strong> — for each name appearing in
          multiple overlays, decide whether it refers to the same concept (single URI) or
          to context-specific concepts (separate URIs with mapping).
        </li>
      </ol>

<script slot="scripts" is:inline data-astro-rerun src="/ui/data-browser.js"></script>
<script slot="scripts" is:inline data-astro-rerun src="/data/properties.js"></script>
<script slot="scripts" is:inline data-astro-rerun>
  // Mount is deferred to astro:page-load so the src scripts above (data-browser.js,
  // properties.js) are guaranteed to have finished loading before this runs.
  // astro:page-load fires after runScripts() on SPA nav AND after window load on
  // hard refresh — both paths land here with window.OPDA and window.OPDA_PROPERTIES set.
  // The handler is stored on window so each re-run (data-astro-rerun) can remove
  // the previous listener, preventing multiple mounts after repeated SPA navigations.
  if (window._opdaDataDictMount) {
    document.removeEventListener('astro:page-load', window._opdaDataDictMount);
  }
  window._opdaDataDictMount = function () {
    function esc(s) { return String(s == null ? '' : s).replace(/[<>&"]/g, c => ({ '<': '&lt;', '>': '&gt;', '&': '&amp;', '"': '&quot;' }[c])); }

    var data = window.OPDA_PROPERTIES || [];
    var mountEl = document.getElementById('elements-browser');
    if (!mountEl) return;
    if (!data.length) {
      mountEl.innerHTML = '<div class="db-empty">Could not load <code>/data/properties.js</code>.</div>';
      return;
    }

    var sourceLabels = {
      'pdtf-transaction': 'Base Transaction',
      'baspi5':    'BASPI v5',
      'rds':       'Residential Data Schema',
      'piq':       'Property Info Questionnaire',
      'ta6':       'Property Information Form',
      'ta7':       'Leasehold Information Form',
      'ta10':      'Fittings & Contents',
      'nts2':      'NTS Sales v2',
      'ntsl2':     'NTS Lettings v2',
      'lpe1':      'Leasehold Property Enquiry',
      'con29R':    'Local Authority Search',
      'con29DW':   'Drainage & Water',
      'fme1':      'Mortgage Enquiries',
      'oc1':       'Office Copy',
      'llc1':      'Local Land Charges',
      'sr24':      'SR24',
    };

    OPDA.DataBrowser.mount({
      mount: mountEl,
      heading: { id: 'browse', text: 'Browse all data elements' },
      data: data,
      itemLabel: 'data elements',
      searchPlaceholder: 'Search name, title or description…',
      searchKeys: ['name', 'title', 'description', 'examplePath'],
      pageSize: 25,
      defaultSort: { key: 'examplePath', dir: 'asc' },
      facets: [
        { key: 'sources', label: 'Source schema', valueLabels: sourceLabels },
        { key: 'kind',    label: 'Kind' },
        { key: 'contexts', label: 'Bounded context' },
        { key: 'type',    label: 'JSON type' },
      ],
      columns: [
        { key: 'kind', label: 'Kind', sortable: true, width: '4%',
          render: function (v) {
            if (!v) return '<span class="muted tiny">—</span>';
            if (v === 'entity') {
              return '<svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" aria-label="entity"><title>Entity (object/array)</title><path d="M2.114 8.063V7.9c1.005-.102 1.497-.615 1.497-1.6V4.503c0-1.094.39-1.538 1.354-1.538h.273V2h-.376C3.25 2 2.49 2.759 2.49 4.352v1.524c0 1.094-.376 1.456-1.49 1.456v1.299c1.114 0 1.49.362 1.49 1.456v1.524c0 1.593.76 2.352 2.372 2.352h.376v-.964h-.273c-.964 0-1.354-.444-1.354-1.538V9.663c0-.984-.492-1.497-1.497-1.6zM13.886 7.9v.163c-1.005.103-1.497.616-1.497 1.6v1.798c0 1.094-.39 1.538-1.354 1.538h-.273v.964h.376c1.613 0 2.372-.759 2.372-2.352v-1.524c0-1.094.376-1.456 1.49-1.456V7.332c-1.114 0-1.49-.362-1.49-1.456V4.352C13.51 2.759 12.75 2 11.138 2h-.376v.964h.273c.964 0 1.354.444 1.354 1.538V6.3c0 .984.492 1.497 1.497 1.6Z"/></svg>';
            }
            return '<svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" aria-label="property"><title>Property (scalar)</title><path d="M2 1a1 1 0 0 0-1 1v4.586a1 1 0 0 0 .293.707l7 7a1 1 0 0 0 1.414 0l4.586-4.586a1 1 0 0 0 0-1.414l-7-7A1 1 0 0 0 6.586 1zm3.5 4a1.5 1.5 0 1 1 0-3 1.5 1.5 0 0 1 0 3"/></svg>';
          }
        },
        { key: 'title', label: 'Title', sortable: true, width: '15%',
          render: function (v) { return v ? esc(v) : '<span class="muted tiny">—</span>'; }
        },
        { key: 'description', label: 'Description', sortable: false, width: '22%',
          render: function (v) { return v ? esc(v) : '<span class="muted tiny">—</span>'; }
        },
        { key: 'type', label: 'Type', sortable: true, width: '6%',
          render: function (v) { return v ? esc(v) : '<span class="muted tiny">—</span>'; }
        },
        { key: 'sources', label: 'In schemas', sortable: false, width: '12%',
          render: function (v, row) {
            if (!v || !v.length) return '<span class="muted tiny">—</span>';
            var primary = row.source || v[0];
            var label = sourceLabels[primary] || primary;
            var extra = v.length > 1 ? ' <span class="muted tiny">+' + (v.length - 1) + '</span>' : '';
            return '<span title="' + esc(v.join(', ')) + '">' + esc(label) + extra + '</span>';
          }
        },
        { key: 'name', label: 'Name', sortable: true, width: '9%',
          render: function (v) { return v ? '<code>' + esc(v) + '</code>' : '<span class="muted tiny">—</span>'; }
        },
        { key: 'examplePath', label: 'Example path', sortable: true, width: '14%',
          render: function (v, row) {
            if (!v) return '<span class="muted tiny">—</span>';
            var suffix = row.pathCount > 1
              ? ' <span class="muted tiny" title="appears at ' + row.pathCount + ' paths">×' + row.pathCount + '</span>'
              : '';
            return '<code>' + esc(v) + '</code>' + suffix;
          }
        },
        { key: 'uri', label: 'Suggested URI', sortable: false, width: '15%',
          render: function (v) {
            if (!v) return '<span class="muted tiny">—</span>';
            var short = v.replace('https://opda.org.uk/pdtf/', 'pdtf:');
            return '<code title="' + esc(v) + '">' + esc(short) + '</code>';
          }
        },
      ],
    });
  };
  document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', window._opdaDataDictMount);
</script>
</Layout>

